BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:qPi-Z54JjOpuyd5wHD20J
SUMMARY:Magnuson Reforestation
DTSTAMP:20260321T221844Z
DTSTART:20260322T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Warren G. Magnuson Park
	. \\nHelp improve habitat and create replacement forest on a formerly denu
	ded navy airfield. (Above photo taken in Navy era). The aim is to create h
	ealthy forest habitat and increase beneficial ecosystem services including
	 provision of human enjoyment and health. It is also an opportunity to enj
	oy nature and learn a bit about native plants while doing satisfying work.
	 \\nWork is most likely to include distributing wood chip mulch and removi
	ng invasive plants like ivy\\\, Canada thistle\\\, and blackberry but may 
	also include other tasks. \\nBecause the work may be beyond capability of 
	youth below high school age\\\, please get the leader’s permission before 
	registering if younger.\\nRegister\n\nhttps://www.seattleparksfoundation.o
	rg/event/magnuson-reforestation-29/\n\nFrom The Seattle Parks Foundation
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/magnuson-reforestation-29/
LOCATION:WA
